<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="contrary-n">contrary <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'kɒntrəri/    美 /'kɑːntreri/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-the">1.★ <strong>[C] [常与the连用] 相反；反面；对立面：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Being too anxious to help an event develop often results in the contrary to our intention.
“拔苗助长”往往会事与愿违。</p><footer>2008 广东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="on-the-contrary">on the contrary</h3>
<p>1.<strong>正相反；恰恰相反：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He thought his marketing plan was perfect, but on the contrary, it was not and it failed.
他以为自己的营销计划完美无缺，而事实恰恰相反，这个计划不仅不完美，还徒劳无功。</p><footer>人教③ – 3</footer></div>

<h3 id="to-the-contrary">to the contrary</h3>
<p>1.<strong>相反的；相反地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Unless I hear anything to the contrary, I shall assume the meeting will be held on time.
除非有人反对，否则我会认为会议将准时召开。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>He seems to be giving the impression that he didn’t enjoy himself in Paris. <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (正相反) he had a wonderful time.  （2012 江西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. On the contrary  </p></div>